Follow these steps to set up and run the assignment. Make sure you have the required libraries and dependencies installed.

**1. Install Node.js and npm:**

Make sure you have Node.js and npm installed.

**2. Navigate to the Project Directory:**
Change your working directory to your project folder:
- cd <assignment-3>

**3. Install Angular CLI:**
Install the Angular Command Line Interface:
- npm install -g @angular/cli

**4. Install Dependencies:**
In your project directory, install the required dependencies using:
- npm install
- npm install mongoose
- npm install bootstrap

**5.  Google Translate and Text-to-Speech:**
To use the text-to-speech/ translate function:
Remember to provide enable them in Google cloud, and key in your key in the terminal using the following command: 

- Linux or macOS: `export GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS="/home/user/Downloads/service-account-file.json"`
- Windows: `$env:GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS="C:\Users\username\Downloads\[FILE_NAME].json"`
- npm install --save @google-cloud/text-to-speech
- npm install --save @google-cloud/translate

**6 Run the Application:**
Start your Angular application using the following command:
- ng build
Open another terminal, and start the server using:
node server.js
Your Angular app will start and should be accessible in a web browser at 'http://localhost:8080/'.